Introduction

Employee is an individual hired as a part-timer of full-timer to complete a specific task, in exchange of wages or salary.

Employee resignation normally happened due to attrition, push factors or pull factors. This is indeed a normal phenomenon but abnormal if resignation happens frequently.

Impact:
  • Loss of talents which indirectly affecting the business performance and productivity.
  • Negative impacts towards organizations in terms of hiring cost, training effort and time invested in long run.
Motivation:
  • Frequent resignations happened among our working companies.
  • The Great Resignation (2021).
  • To have a better understanding of the factors that cause employee attrition.

Project Information

Data Source:
  • Kaggle - IBM Human Resource Data
Questions:
  1. What is the relationship between the factors that cause employee attrition?
  2. Which are the significant factors that influence the employee turnover?
Target Audience:
  1. Company or Organization Human Resource Department
  2. Ministry of Human Resource (MOHR) / Policymakers
Significance:
  1. Insightful information on the root causes of employee churn.
  2. Important guideline for employee retention strategies and enhancement of employee benefits.
  3. Act as a tool to alter employee benefits when recruiting potential talents.

ShinyApp

  • Descriptive Analysis
  • Exploratory Data Analysis

Summary

Churning factors:
  • Work over time -> no work life balance.
  • Job satisfaction & working environment.
Factors of not churning:
  • Working Experience (Age, Income, Job Level)
  • Company / Organisation (Boss, Role, Promotion).
Challenges:
  1. Unbalanced data as the count of employee churner is much lesser in the dataset.
  2. Difficult to get real employee information from companies.
Future Work:
  1. Build prediction model to predict potential employee churner
  2. Include working mode (hybrid or remote) as factor in analysis
